paragraphs.text:
%spark2.r

jobs <- as.data.frame(read.csv(
  'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/nprapps/pym.js/master/examples/graphic/data.csv',
  stringsAsFactors = T
))
jobs$date <- as.Date(paste(jobs$date,'-01',sep=''))

print(names(jobs))
print(head(jobs))

library(ggplot2)
library(scales)
j <- qplot(date, jobs, data=jobs, main='Retail employment', color=jobs) + geom_smooth(aes(group = 1000), size = 1, se = F) + scale_x_date()
ggsave(file='plot.png')

%spark2

show()

paragraphs.text:
%spark2.r

by_tailnum <- group_by(flights, tailnum)
delay <- summarise(by_tailnum,
  count = n(),
  dist = mean(distance, na.rm = TRUE),
  delay = mean(arr_delay, na.rm = TRUE))
delay <- filter(delay, count > 20, dist < 2000)

ggplot(delay, aes(dist, delay)) +
  geom_point(aes(size = count), alpha = 1/2) +
  geom_smooth() +
  scale_size_area()
ggsave(file='plot.png')
show()

%spark2.r

faithful_df <- createDataFrame(sqlContext, faithful)
show(first(faithful_df))
showDF(faithful_df)

# New more R-like APIs in Spark 1.5.0..

showDF(faithful_df[faithful_df$eruptions > 3.0, 2])

showDF(SparkR::transform(faithful_df, waiting2 = faithful_df$waiting / 2))

%sh
cd /tmp
rm -f nycflights13.csv
wget -nv https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/sparkr-data/nycflights13.csv

%spark2.r

# Set this "com.databricks:spark-csv_2.10:1.2.0" to Interpreter property, "zeppelin.sparkr.packages"

flights_df <- read.df(sqlContext,'file:///tmp/nycflights13.csv', 'com.databricks.spark.csv', header='true')
print(names(flights_df))

%spark2.r

by_tailnum_df <- group_by(flights_df, "tailnum")
delay_df <- summarize(by_tailnum_df,
    count = n(flights_df$tailnum),
    dist = mean(flights_df$distance),
    delay = mean(flights_df$arr_delay)))

%spark2.r

# Run a query to print the top 5 most frequent destinations from JFK
jfk_flights <- filter(flights_df, flights_df$origin == "JFK")

# Group the flights by destination and aggregate by the number of flights
dest_flights <- agg(group_by(jfk_flights, jfk_flights$dest), count = n(jfk_flights$dest))

# Now sort by the `count` column and print the first few rows
showDF(arrange(dest_flights, desc(dest_flights$count)))

paragraphs.text:
%sparkr

# Combine the whole query into two lines using magrittr
library(magrittr)
dest_flights <- filter(flights_df, flights_df$origin == "JFK") %>% 
  group_by(flights_df$dest) %>% 
  summarize(count = n(flights_df$dest))

showDF(arrange(dest_flights, desc(dest_flights$count)))

%sparkr

# Running SQL Queries
registerTempTable(flights_df, "flightsTable")
showDF(sql(sqlContext, "SELECT dest, sum(arr_delay) as total_arr_delay FROM flightsTable GROUP BY dest ORDER BY dest asc"))

%sparkr

# In 1.5.0, SparkR allows the fitting of generalized linear models over DataFrames using the glm() function.
# SparkR uses MLlib to train a model of the specified family. Currently the gaussian and binomial families are supported.
# It supports a subset of the available R formula operators for model fitting, including '~', '.', '+', and '-'.

df <- createDataFrame(sqlContext, iris)
model <- glm(Sepal_Length ~ Sepal_Width + Species, data = df, family = "gaussian")
predictions <- predict(model, newData = df)
showDF(predictions)

%sparkr
library(ggplot2)
data(movies)
set.seed(5689)
movies <- movies[sample(nrow(movies), 1000), ]

m <- ggplot(movies, aes(x=rating))
m + geom_histogram(aes(fill = ..count..)) + scale_fill_gradient("Count", low = "green", high = "red")
ggsave(file="plot.png")
show()
